                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-332-off1736 t18220911-332-crimeloc1738"></join>. On the 13th of September I was in the parlour; the servant alarmed me; I ran out and saw the prisoner one door off, walking away. I called Stop thief! and he was taken and brought back. There was another boy with him whom I saw drop the shoes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220911-332-person2926">
                  EDWARD 
                  CHITTENDEN
               <interp inst="t18220911-332-person2926" type="surname" value="CHITTENDEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-332-person2926" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-332-person2926" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shoemaker. My girl alarmed me; I went out and saw the shoes under the prisoner's arm. I caught him - he dropped them - they hung inside the shop. I saw them safe just before I secured both the boys.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The other boy dropped them - I picked them up, and they took me.</p>
